            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>The Trials of Our Fate</head>
                <origin>Boston Press and Post</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p>"At this hour a majority of the Republican party in Massachusetts do inwardly
                        rejoice at the John Brown raid."</p>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>What has the Republic come to when the Virginia governor needs to issue
                    passports for citizens to travel in certain areas of the state? Why can't the
                    good men of New England--the farmers, merchants, etc.-- rally together to ensure
                    that abolitionist fervor doesn't rule?</summary>
            </div>
